commit.message:
changed `AbelianPcpGroup`, `DihedralPcpGroup` (#81)

Now they call the methods for `AbelianGroupCons` and `DihedralGroupCons`,
respectively, which belong to the package.
This way, the `AbelianGroup` fix from #79 works also for `AbelianPcpGroup`,
and now `DihedralPcpGroup(2)` works.

commit.message:
fixed the `AbelianGroupCons` method for `IsPcpGroup`

Generators of order 1 are in principle supported,
but we got an error when all generators had order 1,
and the group was corrupted when some but not all generators had order 1.

See gap-system/gap/issues/5430 for details.
Domain of crossed pairing is GxG not G
Ensure new alnuth for compatibility with new pari
Use SortBy to simplify some code

Fix bug in IsSingleValued

... and possibly also in CoKernelOfMultiplicativeGeneralMapping, although
I have no reproducer for an error there.

Don't make MappedVector read-only

... to avoid warnings, because the GAP library actually
already defines this function.

See also <https://github.com/gap-system/gap/pull/4973>.
Rename WordByExps to avoid clash with other packages

Rename Representation -> RepresentationForPcpCollector

... to avoid potential clashes with other code

Move a UnitriangularMatrixRepresentation method

... so that we don't access Representation before it is defined

Use BindGlobal for most globals

... to avoid accidental redefinitions
